  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main goal of the proposed project is to assess treatment-induced changes of
      electrophysiological and psychophysiological correlates of the capacity to regulate emotion,
      executive functions, and clinical measures in individuals with (complex) posttraumatic stress
      disorder, dissociative disorders, or borderline personality disorder in naturalistic
      inpatient and outpatient settings.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
